================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY DATA AND MODEL NOTICES
================================================================================

This project includes example/orchestration code only. It does NOT bundle any
of the proprietary datasets or model weights referenced below. Operators are
responsible for sourcing, licensing, and providing their own data and weights.

1. E-COMMERCE TRAINING DATA (3C CUSTOMER-SERVICE CONVERSATIONS)
   - All canonical cases, SOP policies and synthetic conversations produced by
     this codebase are seeded from public-domain or self-authored fixtures
     (`src/ecommerce/dataset/fixtures`). No proprietary customer-service
     transcripts are shipped.
   - The data registry (`src/ecommerce/dataset/registry.py`) treats any
     `source_id == "owned_sop_v1"` entry as owned, self-authored material
     suitable for `train` and `evaluate` usage.
   - External sources MUST be registered with an explicit `license_note`
     and the pipeline refuses to use any source whose `usage_permissions`
     does not include the requested flag.

2. FINANCIAL RAG DATA (ANNUAL/POLICY DISCLOSURES)
   - The chunker, parser and retriever operate on documents that you supply.
     This repository ships ONLY a single self-authored fixture at
     `data/fixtures/finance/parsed/fixture_a_2024.json` and a manifest pointing
     to it; nothing in this repo is scraped from Cninfo/SE/PBoC/NDRC or any
     other real disclosure portal.
   - When you add real PDFs, populate `data/raw/reports/document_manifest.json`
     with their original URLs, publisher, publication date, license note and
     a SHA-256 checksum of the bytes.

3. EMBEDDING / GENERATION MODELS
   - The default `RealEmbeddingBackend` references `BAAI/bge-m3`. Operators
     MUST accept the model's license on Hugging Face before downloading and
     pinning the revision in their config.
   - The SFT configs (`configs/train/sft_qwen3_8b.yaml`,
     `sft_llama3_8b.yaml`) reference third-party base models
     (Qwen3-8B, Llama-3-8B-Instruct). Operators MUST accept the relevant
     licenses (Apache-2.0 for Qwen3, the Llama 3 Community License for
     Llama-3) before any training run.
   - DPO is intentionally left experimental; preference data MUST be
     collected and licensed by the operator.

4. NO REDISTRIBUTION
   - The pipeline defaults treat `license_note` values starting with
     `official-disclosure` as `local-research; no-redistribution`. Such
     records may be used for offline evaluation but MUST NOT be re-shared.
